<item>
            <title>[LU-18564] &apos;lfs ost&apos; and &apos;lfs check ost&apos; behave different but are indistinct in the man pages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18564</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lfs ost&lt;/tt&gt; - does not make a network request to report the status, it uses cached values. The clients will communicate independently with the cluster, (sending a ping to OSTs, for example) every 30 seconds or so to refresh their cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lfs check ost&lt;/tt&gt; - makes a RPC against the server during the course of the command.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
